name: Ben Davenport
tweet: @nntaleb 5) Any event that can destroy tens or hundreds of thousands of globally distributed copies of a ledger simultaneously, including those buried in Faraday cages inside mountains is likely to be a species-ending event.

name: Ben Davenport
tweet:
@nntaleb 3) Only one copy of the ledger need survive to preserve Bitcoin. An internet outage does not destroy the ledger, only temporarily partitions the network.

4) By induction, many copies of the ledger will survive at all future times unless all are destroyed simultaneously.

name: Ben Davenport
tweet:
@nntaleb 1) If Bitcoin is important at time T, many copies of the ledger will be maintained and preserved til time T+1.

2) If Bitcoin was important at time T, it is likely to be equally or more important at T+1. (Lindy)
